     "DispatchRateInBytes" : "value"

      • deleteResourceGroup

        void deleteResourceGroup​(java.lang.String resourcegroup)
                  throws PulsarAdminException
        Delete an existing resourcegroup.

        The resourcegroup needs to unused and not attached to any entity.

        Parameters:
        resourcegroup - Resourcegroup name
        Throws:
        PulsarAdminException.NotAuthorizedException - You don't have admin permission
        PulsarAdminException.NotFoundException - Resourcegroup does not exist
        PulsarAdminException.ConflictException - Resourcegroup is in use
        PulsarAdminException - Unexpected error
